WEBVTT

00:10.125 --> 00:11.875
Hey, guys.

00:10.125 --> 00:11.875
Check it out!

00:11.917 --> 00:14.417
Science Bob just sent us tickets

00:11.917 --> 00:14.417
for his live show, Friday night.

00:14.458 --> 00:15.917
I can't wait!

00:15.959 --> 00:19.625
Actually, you can wait.

00:15.959 --> 00:19.625
You just don't want to.

00:19.667 --> 00:23.792
[sighs]

00:19.667 --> 00:23.792
It's a figure of speech, Ricky.

00:23.834 --> 00:26.041
- Ah, front row seats.

00:26.083 --> 00:28.875
We're Science B's VIPs.

00:28.917 --> 00:31.709
I hope he does that experiment

00:28.917 --> 00:31.709
where he turns olive juice

00:31.750 --> 00:35.166
into an olive,

00:31.750 --> 00:35.166
using muscular astronomy.

00:35.208 --> 00:39.834
Actually, it's molecular

00:35.208 --> 00:39.834
gastronomy.

00:39.875 --> 00:42.792
Which is the cooking

00:39.875 --> 00:42.792
or eating of fine food.

00:42.834 --> 00:44.917
[all sighing]

00:44.959 --> 00:48.667
Whatever--as long as I get

00:44.959 --> 00:48.667
to eat that delicious olive.

00:48.709 --> 00:50.875
Technically

00:48.709 --> 00:50.875
if it's made of juice,

00:50.917 --> 00:51.875
you're drinking it.

00:51.917 --> 00:54.375
[all sighing]

00:54.417 --> 00:57.667
Ricky, you don't have

00:54.417 --> 00:57.667
to be right all the time.

00:57.709 --> 01:00.250
Yeah, you're always

00:57.709 --> 01:00.250
correcting us.

01:00.291 --> 01:01.500
I don't always.

01:01.542 --> 01:03.041
In fact, there's

01:01.542 --> 01:03.041
a lot of mistakes

01:03.083 --> 01:07.083
you make that I think--

01:03.083 --> 01:07.083
"Eh, not worth it."

01:07.125 --> 01:09.041
[doorbell rings]

01:11.333 --> 01:12.542
- Hey, Mae!

01:12.583 --> 01:13.875
I got you a ticket

01:12.583 --> 01:13.875
for Science Bob's

01:13.917 --> 01:15.000
show this Friday.

01:15.041 --> 01:17.333
- Get excited!

01:15.041 --> 01:17.333
- I am excited.

01:17.375 --> 01:19.291
But I'm not going.

01:19.333 --> 01:20.542
What-- why?

01:20.583 --> 01:22.375
That's Friday

01:20.583 --> 01:22.375
the 13th.

01:22.417 --> 01:23.667
Friday the 13th

01:22.417 --> 01:23.667
is just a day

01:23.709 --> 01:25.625
like any other day.

01:25.667 --> 01:28.667
You really don't believe

01:25.667 --> 01:28.667
in silly superstitions, do you?

01:28.709 --> 01:31.917
No, not silly ones.

01:28.709 --> 01:31.917
Just real ones.

01:31.959 --> 01:34.875
Like Friday the 13th--

01:31.959 --> 01:34.875
It's bad luck.

01:34.917 --> 01:38.875
In reality, there's no such

01:34.917 --> 01:38.875
thing as bad luck.

01:38.917 --> 01:42.291
Friday the 13th is just

01:38.917 --> 01:42.291
a day like any other day.

01:42.333 --> 01:44.500
- Don't correct my friend.

01:42.333 --> 01:44.500
- But you just said--

01:44.542 --> 01:46.542
Pipe down, friend.

01:46.583 --> 01:48.875
You may know the answers

01:46.583 --> 01:48.875
to hard facts,

01:48.917 --> 01:53.208
but you can't know for sure

01:48.917 --> 01:53.208
superstitions aren't real.

01:53.250 --> 01:55.125
Well, if you believe

01:53.250 --> 01:55.125
in superstitions,

01:55.166 --> 01:58.083
aren't you worried

01:55.166 --> 01:58.083
about stepping on that crack?

01:58.125 --> 02:01.125
Step on a crack,

01:58.125 --> 02:01.125
break your mother's back.

02:01.166 --> 02:02.667
And see?

02:01.166 --> 02:02.667
Nothing happened.

02:02.709 --> 02:05.083
[crash]

02:02.709 --> 02:05.083
[Anne] Ow, my back!

02:06.834 --> 02:08.834
- Mom, are you okay?

02:06.834 --> 02:08.834
- She's fine.

02:08.875 --> 02:10.959
Yeah, I just tweaked

02:08.875 --> 02:10.959
my back carrying in

02:11.000 --> 02:13.959
all the groceries by myself.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.542
I'm sorry, hon.

02:15.583 --> 02:17.709
I was just about

02:15.583 --> 02:17.709
to beat my high score on<i> Grocery</i>

02:15.583 --> 02:17.709
<i>Hero.</i>

02:17.750 --> 02:19.333
You take virtual groceries

02:17.750 --> 02:19.333
and put them away

02:19.375 --> 02:21.250
on virtual shelves.

02:21.291 --> 02:24.458
Sleep tight,

02:21.291 --> 02:24.458
low-fat yogurt.

02:24.500 --> 02:26.041
See, Ricky.

02:26.083 --> 02:28.583
Step on a crack,

02:26.083 --> 02:28.583
break your mother's back.

02:28.625 --> 02:31.083
Actually, Mom's back

02:28.625 --> 02:31.083
isn't broken.

02:31.125 --> 02:32.375
It just hurts.

02:32.417 --> 02:34.375
Besides, this isn't

02:32.417 --> 02:34.375
bad luck.

02:34.417 --> 02:36.083
It's just bad Dad.

02:36.125 --> 02:37.542
Whoa, whoa, whoa,

02:36.125 --> 02:37.542
whoa, whoa, whoa.

02:37.583 --> 02:40.625
- He is not a bad dad.

02:37.583 --> 02:40.625
- I dropped the milk!

02:40.667 --> 02:43.208
He is a bad husband.

02:43.250 --> 02:44.750
Noted.

02:44.792 --> 02:47.375
And I'll pick up

02:44.792 --> 02:47.375
the real groceries.

02:47.417 --> 02:50.667
Excuse me, my atlas

02:47.417 --> 02:50.667
is getting cold.

02:54.417 --> 02:57.375
I am sick of Ricky

02:54.417 --> 02:57.375
being so sure he's right

02:57.417 --> 02:59.125
and always correcting us.

02:59.166 --> 03:02.041
Yeah, and he does

02:59.166 --> 03:02.041
it to me all the time.

03:02.083 --> 03:04.750
Like he's more

03:02.083 --> 03:04.750
smartest than me.

03:04.792 --> 03:08.458
We need to prove he can

03:04.792 --> 03:08.458
be wrong about something.

03:08.500 --> 03:11.667
What if we prove

03:08.500 --> 03:11.667
superstitions are real?

03:11.709 --> 03:13.500
So you do think

03:11.709 --> 03:13.500
they're real?

03:13.542 --> 03:16.041
[snorts] Of course not,

03:13.542 --> 03:16.041
they're ridiculous.

03:16.083 --> 03:17.792
Sorry.

03:17.834 --> 03:19.834
So in order to prove

03:17.834 --> 03:19.834
Ricky's wrong

03:19.875 --> 03:22.625
about superstitions

03:19.875 --> 03:22.625
not being real,

03:22.667 --> 03:25.834
we have to convince

03:22.667 --> 03:25.834
him superstitions are real?

03:25.875 --> 03:28.250
Even though we know

03:25.875 --> 03:28.250
they're not real?

03:28.291 --> 03:29.792
Yeah, exactly.

03:29.834 --> 03:32.792
See, now who's

03:29.834 --> 03:32.792
more smartester?

03:34.959 --> 03:36.625
[upbeat music]

03:36.667 --> 03:40.667
- ♪ Na na na na na na ♪

03:36.667 --> 03:40.667
- ♪ One, two, one, two, three,

03:36.667 --> 03:40.667
four! ♪

03:42.083 --> 03:45.500
[upbeat music]

03:45.542 --> 03:48.792
Okay, I loosened all the screws

03:45.542 --> 03:48.792
in Ricky's chair

03:48.834 --> 03:51.000
so when he sits down,

03:48.834 --> 03:51.000
it'll collapse

03:51.041 --> 03:54.667
because of his "bad luck"

03:51.041 --> 03:54.667
from walking under the ladder.

03:54.709 --> 03:56.458
And then he'll have to admit

03:56.500 --> 03:58.458
he was wrong about

03:56.500 --> 03:58.458
superstitions.

03:58.500 --> 03:59.750
- Are you sure

03:58.500 --> 03:59.750
it's a good idea

03:59.792 --> 04:02.208
to be messing with

03:59.792 --> 04:02.208
superstitions like this?

04:02.250 --> 04:05.166
What if Mae's right and--and

04:02.250 --> 04:05.166
there's something to it?

04:05.208 --> 04:07.083
I think it's a great idea.

04:07.125 --> 04:11.709
It's clever, it's simple,

04:07.125 --> 04:11.709
and it's got the element of

04:07.125 --> 04:11.709
supplies.

04:11.750 --> 04:13.291
You mean surprise?

04:13.333 --> 04:15.375
No, supplies.

04:15.417 --> 04:18.375
We didn't have

04:15.417 --> 04:18.375
to buy any supplies.

04:18.417 --> 04:19.959
That's a good plan.

04:21.792 --> 04:22.959
Sweetie, that's

04:21.792 --> 04:22.959
very nice of you,

04:23.000 --> 04:24.959
but I told you,

04:23.000 --> 04:24.959
my back is fine.

04:25.000 --> 04:25.875
I can fold the laundry.

04:25.917 --> 04:27.166
I know you can,

04:25.917 --> 04:27.166
I just feel bad

04:27.208 --> 04:29.375
about not helping

04:27.208 --> 04:29.375
with the groceries.

04:29.417 --> 04:31.375
Honey, I really appreciate

04:29.417 --> 04:31.375
it but it really--

04:31.417 --> 04:34.083
it's just better when

04:31.417 --> 04:34.083
I do this kind of stuff.

04:34.125 --> 04:35.458
Oh, I see.

04:35.500 --> 04:37.709
It's because I don't

04:35.500 --> 04:37.709
do things the Anne Way.

04:37.750 --> 04:39.792
Huh?

04:39.834 --> 04:42.041
Oh, you know what?

04:39.834 --> 04:42.041
You're right, Tom.

04:42.083 --> 04:44.917
You know, I'm sorry,

04:42.083 --> 04:44.917
I should let you help out around

04:42.083 --> 04:44.917
here more.

04:44.959 --> 04:46.625
Ooh-- I was gonna do

04:44.959 --> 04:46.625
the floors next.

04:46.667 --> 04:47.625
- The floors?

04:46.667 --> 04:47.625
- Yeah.

04:47.667 --> 04:49.417
Well, put me in, coach.

04:49.458 --> 04:50.792
I'm ready to sweep.

04:50.834 --> 04:52.792
- Ohh.

04:50.834 --> 04:52.792
- [chuckles]

05:02.125 --> 05:03.125
Move the chairs!

05:05.166 --> 05:08.417
I'm sorry.

05:05.166 --> 05:08.417
Do it the Tom Way.

05:08.458 --> 05:10.041
Thank you.

05:18.333 --> 05:21.458
Real ma-chair, Anne.

05:21.500 --> 05:26.750
I'm gonna put ma chairs

05:21.500 --> 05:26.750
back where ma want them.

05:28.041 --> 05:31.083
Oh, Ricky?

05:28.041 --> 05:31.083
Lunch time!

05:33.250 --> 05:36.125
You think I'm gonna be afraid

05:33.250 --> 05:36.125
to walk under a ladder?

05:36.166 --> 05:39.583
I told you--

05:36.166 --> 05:39.583
superstitions are bologna.

05:39.625 --> 05:43.750
Are you 100% sure?

05:43.792 --> 05:47.458
Does this answer your question?

05:51.417 --> 05:53.125
What was his answer?

05:53.166 --> 05:55.500
What did you say?

05:55.542 --> 05:56.542
Dicky!

05:56.583 --> 05:57.709
What?

05:57.750 --> 06:00.417
You walked

05:57.750 --> 06:00.417
under the ladder.

06:00.458 --> 06:02.333
I did?

06:02.375 --> 06:05.250
Twice!

06:05.291 --> 06:06.875
And nothing happened,

06:06.917 --> 06:11.041
because there's

06:06.917 --> 06:11.041
no such thing as bad luck.

06:11.083 --> 06:13.500
We'll see about that.

06:15.500 --> 06:20.166
Hey, guys, what do you say we

06:15.500 --> 06:20.166
all sit down for some lunch?

06:20.208 --> 06:21.041
Sure.

06:21.083 --> 06:22.125
Lunch always

06:21.083 --> 06:22.125
tastes better

06:22.166 --> 06:24.083
when you're sitting

06:22.166 --> 06:24.083
in a chair.

06:31.667 --> 06:34.125
Go on-- sit, sit.

06:37.375 --> 06:39.166
[yells]

06:40.542 --> 06:41.959
Dicky, are you okay?

06:43.542 --> 06:45.208
No, he's not okay.

06:45.250 --> 06:48.083
It's bad luck from walking under

06:45.250 --> 06:48.083
that stupid ladder!

06:48.125 --> 06:50.000
Oh, please, I walked

06:48.125 --> 06:50.000
under the ladder

06:50.041 --> 06:51.542
and nothing happened to me.

06:51.583 --> 06:53.291
How do you explain that?

06:53.333 --> 06:54.917
I can't.

06:54.959 --> 06:57.375
But, I can't explain

06:54.959 --> 06:57.375
a lot of things,

06:57.417 --> 07:00.875
like how do all the animals

06:57.417 --> 07:00.875
know where the zoo is?

07:06.291 --> 07:08.875
I saw this on Science Bob's

07:06.291 --> 07:08.875
website.

07:08.917 --> 07:10.792
The vinegar curdles the milk.

07:10.834 --> 07:14.875
Makes it chunky,

07:10.834 --> 07:14.875
sour, and gross.

07:14.917 --> 07:17.083
[all]

07:14.917 --> 07:17.083
Ugh.

07:17.125 --> 07:19.417
All right, so phase two is set.

07:19.458 --> 07:20.709
Now for phase one.

07:20.750 --> 07:22.375
Nicky, where are

07:20.750 --> 07:22.375
the cream puffs?

07:22.417 --> 07:23.083
In the fridge.

07:25.291 --> 07:27.208
Ahh, here they are.

07:27.250 --> 07:30.458
Right above the fresh carton

07:27.250 --> 07:30.458
of milk.

07:30.500 --> 07:33.500
So, we gonna eat them

07:30.500 --> 07:33.500
while we discuss phase one?

07:33.542 --> 07:36.792
No, they are phase one.

07:36.834 --> 07:40.000
Why did phase two

07:36.834 --> 07:40.000
come before phase one?

07:40.041 --> 07:42.542
Did they change math again?

07:42.583 --> 07:45.250
No, math is the same.

07:45.291 --> 07:48.333
Phase one--Ricky eats

07:45.291 --> 07:48.333
the spicy cream puff.

07:48.375 --> 07:49.583
What spicy cream puff?

07:52.333 --> 07:54.041
This spicy cream puff.

07:56.667 --> 07:59.667
Phase two--Ricky drinks

07:56.667 --> 07:59.667
the spoiled milk

07:59.709 --> 08:00.875
to cool his mouth.

08:00.917 --> 08:03.500
Why would he drink

08:00.917 --> 08:03.500
spoiled milk?

08:03.542 --> 08:04.917
'Cause he doesn't know

08:03.542 --> 08:04.917
it's spoiled.

08:04.959 --> 08:06.166
Well then,

08:04.959 --> 08:06.166
who's gonna tell him?

08:06.208 --> 08:07.166
Nobody!

08:07.208 --> 08:08.458
We don't want him to know.

08:08.500 --> 08:10.500
The whole plan revolves

08:08.500 --> 08:10.500
around the element

08:10.542 --> 08:11.959
of not knowing.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.792
Oh, then I'm good.

08:16.041 --> 08:17.959
Now let's go get Ricky.

08:20.917 --> 08:23.083
Ah, looks like Nicky's

08:20.917 --> 08:23.083
been baking.

08:23.125 --> 08:25.583
And left a mess which,

08:23.125 --> 08:25.583
not to worry,

08:25.625 --> 08:27.625
I will clean up.

08:27.667 --> 08:30.792
Oh.

08:27.667 --> 08:30.792
[chuckles]

08:30.834 --> 08:32.583
But honey, I--

08:30.834 --> 08:32.583
I thought you said

08:32.625 --> 08:33.750
you were gonna clean up.

08:33.792 --> 08:36.041
I will.

08:33.792 --> 08:36.041
In Tom time.

08:37.208 --> 08:39.417
But ah--there's milk out.

08:39.458 --> 08:40.792
Noted.

08:42.792 --> 08:45.041
[stammers]

08:42.792 --> 08:45.041
But it's gonna spoil.

08:45.083 --> 08:46.917
You know what, I'm so sorry.

08:45.083 --> 08:46.917
Sorry.

08:46.959 --> 08:49.750
I will let you do it.

08:49.792 --> 08:52.208
But I can't live in Tom time!

08:54.959 --> 08:57.959
Honey,

08:54.959 --> 08:57.959
I said I'd do it!

08:58.000 --> 08:59.500
[sighs]

08:59.542 --> 09:01.667
Everything's gotta be done

08:59.542 --> 09:01.667
the Anne way.

09:03.417 --> 09:05.291
Oh, boy.

09:05.333 --> 09:07.417
Here, let me just--

09:07.458 --> 09:09.166
There we go.

09:09.208 --> 09:13.709
Good thing the floor

09:09.208 --> 09:13.709
is Tom clean.

09:13.750 --> 09:15.875
Well, it's not my hair.

09:18.792 --> 09:22.166
Ooh! Cream puffs!

09:22.208 --> 09:24.250
My favorite!

09:26.083 --> 09:27.500
Mmm...

09:27.542 --> 09:29.125
Mmm...

09:29.166 --> 09:30.625
Mmm...

09:30.667 --> 09:32.417
Uh-oh.

09:32.458 --> 09:35.208
Aaaah!

09:35.250 --> 09:36.667
Fridge!

09:45.667 --> 09:47.917
What the heck?

09:47.959 --> 09:50.917
Yuck. Looks like

09:47.959 --> 09:50.917
that milk is spoiled.

09:56.083 --> 09:58.375
But this one's

09:56.083 --> 09:58.375
fresh as a daisy.

09:58.417 --> 10:01.792
Looks like

09:58.417 --> 10:01.792
it's my lucky day.

10:03.583 --> 10:06.583
You said the good milk

10:03.583 --> 10:06.583
was in the fridge!

10:06.625 --> 10:07.959
It<i> was!</i>

10:08.000 --> 10:09.417
Well, how do you

10:08.000 --> 10:09.417
explain this?

10:09.458 --> 10:11.291
- I can't!

10:09.458 --> 10:11.291
- And the cream puff switch?

10:11.333 --> 10:12.750
- I can't!

10:11.333 --> 10:12.750
- And phase two happening

10:12.792 --> 10:14.041
before phase one?

10:14.083 --> 10:15.750
Okay, I already

10:14.083 --> 10:15.750
explained that.

10:15.792 --> 10:18.333
The rest I can't explain.

10:18.375 --> 10:20.750
Well, I can.

10:18.375 --> 10:20.750
It's bad luck from the ladder!

10:20.792 --> 10:22.834
No, it's not.

10:22.875 --> 10:26.083
Look, we just need

10:22.875 --> 10:26.083
to stick to the plan and

10:22.875 --> 10:26.083
convince Ricky superstitions are

10:22.875 --> 10:26.083
real.

10:26.125 --> 10:28.125
Look, I don't wanna

10:26.125 --> 10:28.125
tempt fate anymore.

10:28.166 --> 10:30.500
- I'm out.

10:28.166 --> 10:30.500
- No! Don't quit now!

10:30.542 --> 10:33.375
Look, we're so close to proving

10:30.542 --> 10:33.375
Ricky wrong about something.

10:33.417 --> 10:35.834
All we have to do

10:33.417 --> 10:35.834
is just come up with a plan

10:35.875 --> 10:38.417
that leaves nothing

10:35.875 --> 10:38.417
to chance.

10:38.458 --> 10:40.792
Our Cousin Chance

10:38.458 --> 10:40.792
from Idaho?

10:40.834 --> 10:43.208
Why would we

10:40.834 --> 10:43.208
